\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Scope and Intake Sources
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy governs two functions.
 First,
 it defines the lifecycle for Corrective Action Plans (CAPs) —
 the documented remediation instruments used to correct deficiencies,
 control failures,
 and compliance gaps identified across the ECIO Policy Manual.
 Second,
 it establishes the compliance monitoring function that verifies the Department's adherence to its incident reporting and breach notification obligations.
 These functions are connected:
 gaps identified through compliance monitoring enter the same CAP lifecycle as deficiencies from any other intake source.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Corrective Action Plans constitute the Department's implementation of NIST SP 800-53 Rev.
 5:
 CA-5 (Plan of Action and Milestones) and CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 CA-5.
 All remediation tracking instruments within the ECIO Policy Manual —
 regardless of the label used in the originating policy —
 shall follow the lifecycle defined in this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall initiate CAPs from the following intake sources.
 This policy does not redefine the triggers or thresholds that generate these inputs;
 it receives them and governs what happens next.
\end_layout

