\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Corrective Action Plan Content and Approval
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall develop a CAP for each deficiency routed to this policy.
 Development shall be completed within ten (10) business days of receipt from the originating source.
 When a deficiency is routed from 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 the ten (10) business day development window begins on the date of classification under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 Section 6.5.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Each CAP shall be documented in the System of Engagement (Redmine) and shall include,
 at minimum,
 the following content:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Deficiency Description
\series default
:
 A clear statement of the control failure,
 compliance gap,
 or process breakdown,
 including the originating source and the affected policy or control.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Root Cause
\series default
:
 The identified or probable cause of the deficiency.
 Where the root cause cannot be determined within the development window,
 the CAP shall state that root cause analysis is ongoing and shall include a milestone for completing it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Remediation Actions
\series default
:
 The specific actions required to correct the deficiency,
 stated with sufficient precision that completion is objectively verifiable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Milestones
\series default
:
 Each CAP shall include one or more defined milestones with target completion dates.
 Milestones shall represent measurable interim checkpoints —
 not a single end-state target.
 The milestone structure shall be sufficient to enable progress tracking and early detection of delays.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Verification Criteria
\series default
:
 The standard by which remediation will be confirmed complete.
 Verification criteria shall identify the assessment method (control re-test,
 self-assessment,
 or audit) and the expected evidence of remediation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Responsible Role
\series default
:
 The role assigned to execute remediation actions.
 Assignment shall follow the role definitions established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Workforce Roles,
 Responsibilities,
 and Competency Framework).
\end_layout

