\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Tracking and Update Cadence
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall maintain all open CAPs in the System of Engagement (Redmine).
 The Assistant IT Director shall review all open CAPs no less than monthly and shall update milestone status upon the completion of any milestone,
 upon discovery of a delay,
 or no less than monthly.
 Each monthly review shall document:
 milestone completion status,
 any changes to the remediation approach or timeline,
 and an assessment of whether the CAP remains on track for closure within its approved timeline.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall update CAPs whenever new information becomes available from control assessments,
 independent audits or reviews,
 or continuous monitoring activities,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 CA-5,
 which requires updates at least every six (6) months or when new information is available.
 The monthly review cadence established in this policy meets and exceeds this minimum.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall report open CAPs through the existing reporting structures established in the manual.
 Open CAPs and their current status shall be included in the monthly performance summary defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 Section 6.4.
 Open CAPs shall be available as an input to the annual policy review and maturity scoring process under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 This policy does not establish separate reporting cadences or standalone CAP status reports.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
When a CAP milestone target date is missed,
 the Assistant IT Director shall document the reason for the delay and establish a revised target date.
 When two (2) or more milestones within a single CAP are missed,
 the Assistant IT Director shall escalate the CAP to the IT Director for review.
 The IT Director shall determine whether the CAP requires revision,
 additional resources,
 or risk acceptance for the underlying deficiency in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
