\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Verification and Closure
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall verify remediation before a CAP is closed.
 The Assistant IT Director shall request verification through the assessment mechanisms defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 —
 control re-test,
 self-assessment,
 or audit —
 appropriate to the nature of the original deficiency.
 This policy does not establish a separate verification methodology;
 it uses the assessment infrastructure that 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 already provides.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The verification assessment shall confirm that the remediation actions have been implemented,
 are operating as intended,
 and are producing the desired outcome —
 the same standard used for the "Conforming" classification in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 Section 6.5.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
A CAP shall not be closed solely on the basis of task completion.
 Closure requires documented verification that the remediation achieved the stated control,
 process,
 or compliance outcome.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Upon receipt of a conforming verification result,
 the Assistant IT Director shall prepare the CAP for closure and submit it to the IT Director with the verification evidence.
 The IT Director shall approve the closure.
 Upon closure,
 the Assistant IT Director shall update the corresponding Risk Register entry under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 to reflect the resolved status.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
When verification reveals that remediation was not effective,
 the Assistant IT Director shall not close the CAP.
 The Assistant IT Director shall revise the remediation approach,
 establish new milestones,
 and resubmit the revised CAP to the IT Director for approval.
\end_layout

